App like a digital bank (NovaPay) where everything happens behind the scenes through services.

🔄 1. User Login (Entry Point)

👉 What happens:

User logs in from frontend
Request goes to Auth Service (Node.js)
Backend:
Verifies email/password
Generates JWT token
Sends token to frontend

👉 This token is used for all future requests

📊 2. Dashboard Load (After Login)
4

👉 What happens:

Frontend calls /dashboard
Backend:
Account Service → fetch balances
Transaction Service → fetch recent transactions
Combines data → sends to UI

👉 Output:

Balance
Spending graph
Notifications
🏦 3. Account Management

👉 What happens:

User views accounts
Backend:
/accounts API
Fetch:
Account details
Transaction history

👉 Used for:

Balance display
Transaction tracking
💸 4. Transfer Money

👉 What happens when user clicks Transfer:

Flow:
Frontend → /transfer
Backend (Node.js):
Validate request
Check balance
Deduct from sender
Add to receiver
Save transaction

👉 Important:

Done safely to avoid:
Double deduction
Failed transfers
